transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. This is Jimmy. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir. My name is Mike McDonald. I got an order, your order a couple days ago.

Speaker 1: I wanted to make sure that you shipped me the right product.

Speaker 2: I'm driving to you. Can you identify me with a phone number and address?

Speaker 1: Yes. I was able to pull that up.

Speaker 2: I'm looking at your order now, Mike.

Speaker 1: You've got the Viagra 50 milligrams. You've got 40 of them.

Speaker 2: Did you order online? I'm just curious.

Speaker 1: Were you trying to get the AGB? Is that what the situation was?

Speaker 2: You were trying to order the AGB?

Speaker 1: Yes, that's what I ordered.

Speaker 2: You got the generic Viagra. I'm going to get that corrected for you right now.

Speaker 1: I'm going to get those shipped out to you at no charge to get you the right order to you.

Speaker 2: Unfortunately, when you go online, sometimes there's a little hiccup.

Speaker 1: For some reason, the farmers get it mixed up sometimes with the regular Viagra.

Speaker 2: I'm going to get those sent out to you. Do me a favor, Michael.

Speaker 1: The next time you want to order, just give us a call so we'll make sure you get the right order.

Speaker 2: Because if you go online again, the same problem might hit.

Speaker 1: I don't want that to be the case for you.

Speaker 2: Okay. Well, I won't do it. I appreciate you handling it professionally.

Speaker 1: Not a problem. No, no. You should get that.

Speaker 2: Let me tell you the difference of the pill, though.

Speaker 1: It's going to be a white-shaped diamond pill, and it's going to have the number 100 on the back,

Speaker 2: and that's how you're going to know it's the AGB Viagra,

Speaker 1: and you're going to see the difference when you try it, too, as well.

Speaker 2: All right?

Speaker 1: Okay, man. Thanks. I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Not a problem. Have a great day.

Speaker 1: See you.

Speaker 2: Thanks.

Speaker 1: You, too.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
